om/ucatandthefiddle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cat and the Fiddle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 12:54:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1485.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More than one character.... let the debate begin...</span><hr size=1> I do own two accounts in a round-about way.  Last year I purchased a second account for my nephew...who although being an avid player, has no intention of ever role-playing.  So, when he is not on his account, I play on Firiona Vie with my second character.  I feel less guilty about the money as long as it's not just for the purchase of an alternate character. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uquethgemsmithe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queth Gemsmithe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/5/02 8:05:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1485.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~azzerhoden/Queth_Head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No Difference</span><hr size=1> There is no difference between twinking a secondary character and twinking someone else's low level character.<br>
<br>
This is an issue that I am oppsoing feelings over.  On the one hand I love the server and would hate to see something like this ruin it.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I do get bored playing an enchanter sometimes.  For those who would add that I should play on a different server I would if they had the trivial loot code in place.  Since they don't, I won't. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anrae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/6/02 5:50:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1485.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No Difference</span><hr size=1> $120.00 is all you have paid?  *rolls her eyes*<br>
<br>
You will find no sympathy here, bucko.  Everquest is this household's most expensive hobby.  We have spent close to... *does the math in her head and winces* umm... lets not go there... shall we?  How we do LOVE our Everquest.<br>
<br>
Oh but back to the topic at hand... <br>
<br>
Don't complain about the amount of money it costs you to play the game or the restrictions placed upon the server.  There are other options... <br>
<br>
Option one... be happy with what you have and quit trying to change things to suit your own wants and needs...<br>
<br>
Option two... go to one of the many servers with multiple slots just beckoning you to create your many alter egos...<br>
<br>
Option three... cancel your account before it is too late... <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
