<br>
I feedback for this every couple of days, I want a bloody second char I can solo with.<br>
<br>
Well, off I go to play on someone else's account because im waiting for someone with mine and have no group.<br>
<br>
Yup, second toon allowed is REALLY needed.<br>
<br>
Also, if I get too bored on my own account,  I will reroll into someone who can solo and twink that toon with about 10000plats of stuff simply because, I am bored, can't get a group, and can't make a second toon to fight with.  Hell, half my guild is now on another server because they are bored with FV and not able to make a second toon when their first is bored. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umelmell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melmell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theorderofthedragon.com/docs/fanart/cross.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>A_Idiot_666</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 12:18:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1485.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://imagem.webphotos.iwon.com/1000032078/1000032078_225200284817PM0.1818354.jpg height=200 width=106></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> Sorry. But that is a consequence with coming to FV. You have a char you pick and play. That char becomes like, you 'life' if you know what I mean. No second chances, no becoming other characters, the reputation you make is the fucking reputation you keep. <br>
<br>
Go ahead and let your character commit suicide aka visit the deletion button for a cup of tea but gotta think about it in the long run. Will you regret it? Did you do all that 'work' for nothing? Many of your friends going to lose contact with you? Be prepared because the only way you can even get close to playing 2 characters online is 2 accounts. You can't even play 2 chars online when your on one account... Always one char per server. So really, I guess getting another account is benefited in both ways....<br>
<br>
I have no clue how you like it but I'm just saying. This is an EZBOARD msgboard, not the Official EQ Msgboards... Go to Everquest.com and search those out. Not much will be affected. <p><center><img src="http://www.morbidangel.com/images/malogonew_off.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 657<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 7:52:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1485.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> GMs at least ..</span><hr size=1> .. do read <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> this</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> board.  I suspect others from Verant do as well.  That doesn't mean they will ever do anything about anything brought up here, but they are aware of what we say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 378<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 3:48:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1485.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Why do people keep saying 'pay for 2 accounts'... I don't even like the game enough to pay for one so I normally only play about 6 months a year and cancel it.<br>
<br>
Frankly, if people refused to pay for 2 accounts, I'm sure Verant would change some rules around because of the incoming stiffer competition.  Fantasy might have the edge, but let me tell you when Star Wars comes out, we're gonna see who rules this world, SciFi geeks or Fantasy geeks.<br>
<br>
Bjond, you sure GM's read these boards?  I always liked boards where the people you talk about actually answer (like some DVD boards where people who run the dot com's will always be around to defend themselves).  Maybe GM's read the board, but more than likely guides do not.<br>
<br>
Hello irony... Sony is running the show on Star Wars Galaxies... uggh, I can't wait for another company to have a breakthrough game to put real competition on VI.<br>
